BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ed3534257860f9a4738515fa10d79140
SUMMARY:[EVENT SERIES] Government Innovation Week Federal
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260224
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260225
LOCATION:University of Ottawa & Ottawa Conference & Event Centre, Ottawa
DESCRIPTION:Innovate to elevate: Unlocking the path to progressive governance As we move into 2026, public sector transformation and innovation remain crucial for shaping responsive and resilient governance. The evolution from Gov 2.0's digital services to Gov 3.0's intelligent, integrated systems offers governments unprecedented opportunities to enhance service delivery, improve efficiency, and foster greater civic engagement—aligning with the federal government's commitment to digital government and service excellence. By embracing smart technologies, data analytics, and AI, public administrations can do more with less, boost productivity, and ensure policies are more adaptive to citizens' evolving needs through personalized, proactive governance. This transformation involves cultivating a culture of continuous improvement and innovation within public entities, maximizing impact with constrained resources.Government Innovation Week Federal brings together Federal leaders to integrate Gov 3.0 innovations while safeguarding equity, privacy, and security—core priorities of the current government's mandate. Join us to explore strategies for navigating digital transformation complexities, enhancing operational productivity, and prioritizing accessibility to bridge the digital divide, supporting the government's commitment to inclusive digital services. Register now to connect with experts from Public Safety Canada, Export Development Canada, Service Canada, the Department of National Defence, and more, engage in meaningful discussions, and be part of the movement setting a new benchmark for governance in the digital age. Link: https://publicsectornetwork.com/events/government-innovation-week-federal-ottawa-2026/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:30b844e64825ebe0956d5bc2269a6868
SUMMARY:[CALL FOR SUBMISSIONS] OECD Call for Government Innovations 2026 Edition
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260224
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260331
LOCATION:Online / Global
DESCRIPTION:The 8th OECD Call for Government Innovations invites global submissions from public servants and those working closely with the public sector. The call aims to identify and share new, implemented, and impactful innovations, particularly across themes like simplifying government, citizen-government relationships, and measuring efficiency/effectiveness. Selected cases will be published in the OPSI Case Study Library and the 2026 OECD report, with outstanding shortlisted cases invited to a global showcase event in Paris. Link: https://oecd-opsi.org/blog/the-oecd-call-for-government-innovations-2026-edition/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d490fa44810f5a0f7c4cf528c59fecaf
SUMMARY:[REPORT] GovTech Trends 2026: A government perspective
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260101
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261231
LOCATION:
DESCRIPTION:This report provides a government-specific take on Deloitte’s Tech Trends 2026, spotlighting the accelerating technology trends most likely to disrupt enterprise IT over the next 18 to 24 months. It explores innovations most relevant for governments and assesses their readiness to scale, focusing on how public sector organizations can harness emerging technologies, especially AI, to redesign processes, align investments with mission objectives, and transform operations for the future. Key topics include 'AI goes physical: Navigating the convergence of AI and robotics' and 'The agentic reality check: Preparing for a silicon-based workforce'. Link: https://www.deloitte.com/us/en/Industries/government-public/articles/government-tech-trends.html
END:VEVENT
